Presenting the state of the economy in Parliament today, Minister for Finance and Planning, Dr Philip Mpango said the growth per capita in US dollars terms increased to 979.1 US dollars last year from 967.5 US dollars in 2015.This suggests that the country needs to boost productivity, value and volume of exports and reduce imports.According to the World Bank, the Middle Income Countries (MICs) are defined as having a per capita gross national income of 1,026 US dollars to 12,475 US dollars.